detail.title: Increase Max Validator Set Size to 64
detail.description:
Through a series of on-chain proposals, we propose to incrementally increase the maximum number of active validators from 32 to 64. The plan is to methodically carry out this expansion across four distinct proposals, with each adding 8 validators to the set. This approach ensures a smooth and controlled transition, whilst providing opportunities for monitoring and potential optimization.
The proposed change is expected to have a minimal to no impact on throughput and block time, thereby preserving the network's operational efficiency and performance. Importantly, it facilitates broader community participation and offers increased incentivization opportunities to network participants. We are confident that this transition will enhance a more robust, scalable, and sustainable ecosystem, thereby reinforcing the ethos of active engagement within our network. Upon the passing of this proposal, the maximum number of validators will be increased to 64.

detail.title: Coreum v2 upgrade
detail.description:
The implementation of Coreum Version 2 has been successfully completed. This milestone enhances the blockchain ecosystem significantly, with notable upgrades in the functionality of Fungible Tokens \(FTs\) and Non-Fungible Tokens \(NFTs\).

Here are the recent developments:

Fungible Tokens \(FTs\):
- Inter-Blockchain Communication \(IBC\) Integration: This integration streamlines connections with other blockchain ecosystems.
- Upgrade Mechanism: This mechanism allows older assets to support new features. After the upgrade, issuers may opt-in for these features.
- Full Balance Details Query: Enables comprehensive balance details per account view.
- New CLI Commands: Addition of novel CLI commands for better control and functionality.

Non-Fungible Tokens \(NFTs\):
- Query NFT Classes: Feature to fetch a detailed list of NFT classes by issuer.
- Fetch Burnt NFTs: Capability to list burnt NFTs.
- New CLI Commands: Introduction of new CLI commands to expand functionality.

WASM:
- IBC Integration: Enabling of the Inter-Blockchain Communication \(IBC\) for the WASM smart contracts.
- WASM SDK: Inclusion of new FTs and NFTs functionalities in the WASM SDK.

Feemodel:
- Query recommended gas price: Facility to fetch the gas price prediction for future blocks to optimize transactions cost.

In case of queries or a requirement for assistance regarding these updates, the support team is available for guidance.
